                        <p>The research also found that the gender gap in earning one-percent income has not changed since the mid- to late- ’90s.&nbsp;</p>
<p>“[The study] shows that so little has changed in women’s income over decades," Keister said. "In the ’80s, we thought, ‘things are changing’ and ‘we are going to have it our way,’ but things aren’t really changing.”</p>

